# NOTE STYLE RULES
Strictly adhere to these formatting structures for all notes.

## 1. COLLAPSIBLE SECTIONS
Use `<Callout>` component (`src/components/Callout.astro`).
Import: `import Callout from '[path-to]/components/Callout.astro';`

| Use Case | Component Template |
| :--- | :--- |
| **Worked Examples** | `<Callout type="example" title="Worked Example: [Topic]" collapsible defaultOpen={false}> ... </Callout>` |
| **Derivations** | `<Callout type="note" title="Derivation: [Topic]" collapsible defaultOpen={false}> ... </Callout>` |
| **Detours / Explorations** | `<Callout type="tip" title="Exploration: [Topic]" collapsible defaultOpen={false}> ... </Callout>` |
| **Warnings** | `<Callout type="warning" title="[Title]" collapsible defaultOpen={false}> ... </Callout>` |

## 2. MATH EQUATION HIGHLIGHTS
DO NOT use KaTeX `\boxed{}`. Wrap `$$` blocks in target `<div>` classes.
CRITICAL: Include blank lines before and after `$$` so MDX parses it as block math.

### Intermediate / Important Steps
Use `math-step` (blue border highlight).
```mdx
<div class="math-step">

$$
[equation]
$$

</div>
```

### Final Results / Pivotal Formulas
Use `math-result` (gradient background + shadow + border).
```mdx
<div class="math-result">

$$
[equation]
$$

</div>
```

## 3. CONSTRAINTS
- Do NOT use inline CSS.
- Do NOT create new Callout types; use only `note`, `tip`, `example`, `warning`.
- Math wrappers must have empty lines around `$$` blocks.
